{"word":"δέσμιος","slug":"δέσμιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δέσμιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δεσμός'><el>δεσμός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>binding</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>binding as with a spell, enchaining</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ὕμνος δ. φρενῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>bound, in bonds, captive</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}